## 1. Download Video
[Learn more about the HTTP Request node]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}

In this demonstration, we'll download a stock video from pixabay using the HTTP Request node. Feel free to use other sources but ensure they are in a format support by OpenCV ([See docs]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}

## 4. Generate Voice Over Clip Using TTS
[Read more about the OpenAI node]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}

Finally with our generated script parts, we can combine them into one and use OpenAI's Audio generation capabilities to generate a voice over from the full script. Once we have the output mp3, we can upload it to somewhere like Google Drive for later use.

Have a listen to the finished product here: {{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}

**The video used in this demonstration is**
&copy; [Coverr-Free-Footage]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }} via [Pixabay]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}
![]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}

